Ars Centurion
Registered: Oct 31, 2013Posts: 286
Posted: Wed Nov 13, 2013 11:58 am
Jeremy2013 wrote:Who blocked the playing of certain Amazon.com video content on Google Chromecast?The Chromecast runs into video licensing problems iirc. Some videos on Amazon, Netflix, Hulu, whatever, are specifically licensed to play on a computer but not a TV. Amazon is contractually required to block those videos if they know you're using a television to watch them, as in the case of a Chromecast.How a television is any different from a monitor, I have no fucking idea. But that's how the contracts are. If you ran an HDMI cable from your PC to your TV, you could watch just fine because it counts as watching via your computer, but stream via Chromecast and the same screen becomes a television.
